{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771508583,"nonce":"vlgMhuelyN1Of7bc5pwabBzAmxk=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87sN54U","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/231","origin":"github"},"title":"Add VS Code setup guide and enable compile_commands.json in build","message":"## Summary\n\nAdd documentation and build support for using VS Code with the workspace.\n\n## Changes Needed\n\n### 1. Enable `compile_commands.json` generation in `build.sh`\n\nAdd `--cmake-args -DCMAKE_EXPORT_COMPILE_COMMANDS=ON` to the `colcon build` invocation in `.agent/scripts/build.sh`. This generates `compile_commands.json` in each package's build directory, enabling C++ IntelliSense in any editor/LSP that supports it.\n\n### 2. Add VS Code setup guide\n\nCreate a documentation file describing how to set up VS Code for this workspace:\n\n- **Multi-root workspace**: Create a `.code-workspace` file referencing the root and each layer as separate folders\n- **Makefile tasks**: Configure `.vscode/tasks.json` at the root to wrap Makefile targets (build, test, lint, status, clean)\n- **C++ IntelliSense**: Point `c_cpp_properties.json` at the per-layer `compile_commands.json`\n- **Python IntelliSense**: Configure `python.analysis.extraPaths` for ROS Python packages\n- **Note**: VS Code config files should be local/untracked — the guide provides instructions, not checked-in configs\n\n### Non-goals\n\n- Do not check in `.vscode/` directories or `.code-workspace` files\n- Do not add VS Code as a dependency or requirement\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}